</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="10238ACF6B00943ACE2B5B713633712E" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="544EAC86F2D26784341FD6A767FF5584" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A48FB6294CBB9126B8091D1BC063FFCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
The generic name is composed of the Latin prefix 
<emphasis id="2A1A1449EE12CF7C713391BEB7C479E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">stria</emphasis>
, referring to the dense striation covering most of the body and 
<emphasis id="4C80E9CDAFF8ADDE73BFE899227AE7DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">stigmus</emphasis>
referring to the large stigma of 
<taxonomicName id="83B5241DD59D86A0E5A455E0861F7B0F" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
. Masculine gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7C49BE2D6450E926567693ABAD12AD3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A77D9FD21313DF6E59D6A0C71BEF2A76" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DEAAEB956A8D1DBDD24111C37FE5517" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Recognized from other 
<taxonomicName id="DDD7C8AD9D5DAA3BD84A447721A67DAA" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
by having circular head shape with concentric striated sculpture on most of face (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AAE466756BF4E66CB31A8616810CC6D7" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Toruli situated low on head with lower margin slightly above lower margin of eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F72D14AA10204521D1D6DA3B2D8753E4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Scrobes shallow, smooth and narrowly triangular, not reaching median ocellus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7280A19ACC91A2AE7F7FB90E8BFCF09B" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1D</figureCitation>
). Most setation on upper face long and black, shorter and white on lower face. Gena smooth and shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7A07E27066419B687AF03159E8F9309A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1C</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina raised, sharp, its dorsal part reaching vertex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DC1C7AA640C663C1F79AA524C7BD4F8E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna slightly clavate with a conspicuous micropilosity area on last clavomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D7BF2F6798F1D0DC0A861D9857576FDF" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum elongated, collar margined and more than half as long as mesoscutum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92D6B2D01E7715EE7C4D8799E2E97AE0" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Anterior half of collar with ten transverse carinae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F5A1D98F2D6A152723942A4687F290B8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum coarsely cross striated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="761434B97E789BE10BE3E3C037BCC38A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutellum delimited anterolaterally from mesoscutum and axillae by broad foveate-septated scutoscutellar sulcus separating axillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="420EB8D64344434B94E81BECCB590E8E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Frenum coarsely reticulated, extending on about half length of mesoscutellum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="639C72694A4BF7CB6674E80DBBC51710" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Propodeum relatively long, area between spiracles coarsely cross striated in proximal part, striate in distal part of propodeum medially turning backwards to propodeal foramen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEB8478FF4215AD38DCB8D73E21C4AA1" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1G</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma dorsally with scarce long black setae, three long white setae laterally on pronotal collar, one on mesoscutal lateral lobe and three smaller ones on axilla along scutoscutellar suture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="043B6D717A044BE059106C917DF95ADA" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1B</figureCitation>
). Hind coxa bare dorsally. Fore wing with marginal vein about as long as postmarginal vein, stigma enlarged, ovoid, basal vein present (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="79EB87924406E6DB8DEB613DA270EC88" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1F</figureCitation>
). Petiole elongated, about 0.8
<normalizedToken id="B57474092364F90043B16302106F9C5F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as propodeum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="43E75E51D3522F2368ADCFEF142E8D20" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1G</figureCitation>
). Metasoma, not including petiole, shorter than mesosoma, smooth or with traces of coriaceous sculpture laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4FD0B91713536FE4698FEB3495BEA6C7" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
), Gt1-2 medially slightly emarginated. Ovipositor upturned and slightly longer than the entire metasoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5E6D3007BAAD138D55DB37C298F83866" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Striastigmus bicoloratus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B mesosoma, dorsal view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F venation G propodeum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm except for habitus (1 mm)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="A99844D4E7A1BA7D3238F97A1AE70696" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677673" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="8CBBB83DC3655585FB0AF8C94F118C77" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="297A16527ED2ACE85A701BE97B676507" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Figure 1.</emphasis>
